# Radix UI Components

Use [@radix-ui/*](https://www.radix-ui.com/primitives) primitives for interactive UI in KidStory. Wrap them in [`src/components/ui/`](src/components/ui/) with Tailwind styling via `cn()`.

Do **not** use `@luckyluu/wonder-ui`.

## When to use

- **New interactive UI** (progress, dialogs, tabs, etc.) → add a Radix primitive wrapper under `src/components/ui/`.
- **Layout and page structure** → Tailwind utility classes alongside Radix wrappers.
- **Existing custom components** → do not rewrite unless the task explicitly asks for it.

## Pattern

```tsx
// src/components/ui/Progress.tsx
import * as ProgressPrimitive from "@radix-ui/react-progress";
import { cn } from "../../lib/utils";

export function Progress({ value, max = 100, className }: ProgressProps) {
  // Root + Indicator, styled with Tailwind
}
```

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD — Radix wrapper for UI primitives
import { Progress } from "../ui";

<Progress value={current + 1} max={total} aria-label={`Card ${current + 1} of ${total}`} />

// ❌ BAD — reintroducing wonder-ui
import { Stepper } from "@luckyluu/wonder-ui";
```

## Established components

| Component | Package | Location |
|-----------|---------|----------|
| `Progress` | `@radix-ui/react-progress` | `src/components/ui/Progress.tsx` |

Add new Radix wrappers to `src/components/ui/` and export from `src/components/ui/index.ts`.
